<figure>
    <figcaption>Sidebar mobile</figcaption>
    <p>
        Sidebar can be optional with additional <code>.sidebar-mobile</code> class.
        Position is <code>fixed</code> on mobile deveices, and default breakpoint is <code>992px</code>.
    </p>
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary toggle-show d-lg-none" data-show="sidebarMobile">Toggle mobile sidebar</a>

    <div class="sidebar sidebar-mobile bg-white" id="sidebarMobile">
        <div class="sidebar-content">
            <div class="p-3">
                <p>This is <code>.sidebar .sidebar-mobile</code> for mobile content.</p>
                <p>On desktop devices position is static, but on portable devices will be hidden and it can be initilized with toggle event as on previous examples. </p>
                <p>Be sure to hide triggers on same brakepoint, in this case class is <code>.d-lg-none</code>.</p>
                <p>Resize the viewport to see the demo!</p>
                <a href="#" class="toggle-show d-lg-none" data-show="sidebarMobile">Close mobile sidebar</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</figure>
